					<td>
					

						<div class="postbody">I suppose, but I wanted to learn more about general tendencies and a set of general, practical guidelines. Four-part writing seems to be more like a learning how to solve musical crossword puzzles than a practical set of guidelines. You sit down with your puzzle, solve it according to a theorist's guidelines, listen to it, and by virtue of the many, many rules, it doesn't sound bad. I honestly can't imagine any one composing in the way four-part harmony puzzles are solved.</div>

